Recent work by [DBLP:conf/acl/RamosRWFL24,DBLP:conf/wsdm/TorbatiTW24] takes advantage of large language models to generate short user profiles from 
reviews and item descriptions. Our framework subsumes this approach as a special case.
The brand-new work of [DongFangLauw:WSDM2025] 
includes reviews 
in learning a model 
over a shared latent space. 
In contrast, our framework makes user profiles explicit before feeding them into the recommender, giving the user a chance to inspect and edit this personal data.